<!-- ======= Framework Section ======= -->
<section id="framework" class="padd-section text-center">
    <div class="container" data-aos="fade-up">
      <div class="section-title text-center">
        <h2>Framework Features.</h2>
        <img src="assets/img/framework/logo.svg" width="120px" height="120px" alt="Next2D Framework">
        <p class="separator">Support systematic team development.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="row" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100">

        <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3">
          <div class="feature-block">
            <img loading="lazy" src="assets/img/framework/feature-01.svg" width="60px" height="60px" alt="Open Source">
            <h4>Open Source</h4>
            <p>Next2D Framework is available free of charge as open source software for personal and commercial use.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3">
          <div class="feature-block">
            <img loading="lazy" src="assets/img/framework/feature-02.svg" width="60px" height="60px" alt="Quick Start">
            <h4>Quick Start</h4>
            <p>You can create a Next2D app by simply executing one command without any build settings.<br>[Command]<br>npx create-next2d-app app-name</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3">
          <div class="feature-block">
            <img loading="lazy" src="assets/img/framework/feature-03.svg" width="60px" height="60px" alt="MVVM pattern.">
            <h4>MVVM pattern</h4>
            <p>Model-View-ViewModel (MVVM) pattern, looking toward a future where UI designers and programmers collaborate to create applications.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3">
          <div class="feature-block">
            <img loading="lazy" src="assets/img/framework/feature-04.svg" width="60px" height="60px" alt="team development">
            <h4>team development</h4>
            <p>Fixed development pattern (MVVM) for readability and simplified sharing.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3">
          <div class="feature-block">
            <img loading="lazy" src="assets/img/framework/feature-05.svg" width="60px" height="60px" alt="Work with NoCode Tool">
            <h4>Work with NoCode Tool</h4>
            <p>As in the Flash era, symbol management is possible, allowing animators and programmers to create applications without conflicts.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3">
          <div class="feature-block">
            <img loading="lazy" src="assets/img/framework/feature-06.svg" width="60px" height="60px" alt="Single Page Application">
            <h4>Single Page Application</h4>
            <p>It is now possible to manage scenes by URL, which has been difficult with previous Canvas/WebGL applications.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3">
          <div class="feature-block">
            <img loading="lazy" src="assets/img/framework/feature-07.svg" width="60px" height="60px" alt="OUTPUT">
            <h4>OUTPUT</h4>
            <p>You can easily export each environment and consolidate the files into one.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3">
          <div class="feature-block">
            <img loading="lazy" src="assets/img/framework/feature-08.svg" width="60px" height="60px" alt="Documentation and Tutorials">
            <h4>Documentation/Tutorials</h4>
            <p>Extensive documentation and tutorials to support you from initial learning to practical use.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>


      <nav class="feature-nav">
        <ul class="list-unstyled">
          <li><a href="https://github.com/Next2D/Framework" class="btn"><i class="bi bi-github"></i> GitHub</a></li>
